\section{Reproducibility}
\label{app:repro}

The study uses the local \texttt{cqed\_sim} framework~\cite{cqed_sim} together with the study-specific helper module. The primary machine-readable outputs are the unconditional-displacement artifacts:
\begin{itemize}
  \item \path{unconditional_displacement_summary.json}
  \item \path{unconditional_single_tone_summary.json}
  \item \path{unconditional_two_tone_summary.json}
  \item \path{unconditional_echo_summary.json}
  \item \path{unconditional_optimal_control_summary.json}
  \item \path{unconditional_protocol_comparison.json}
  \item \path{unconditional_wigner_cases.json}
  \item \path{unconditional_validation_spotcheck.json}
\end{itemize}

The report figures are regenerated from the main unconditional-displacement driver and the auxiliary optimal-waveform plotting step. The reproducibility notebook loads the saved artifacts by default and includes a rerun path for the main driver. A complete reproduction sequence is:
\begin{enumerate}
  \item run the unconditional-displacement driver to regenerate the protocol artifacts and figures,
  \item run the spot-check validation script to regenerate the direct convergence artifact,
  \item regenerate the optimal-control waveform figure from the saved optimal-control artifact,
  \item open the reproducibility notebook to inspect the saved outputs or rerun the workflow with modified parameters.
\end{enumerate}

